Nollywood actress, Kemi Afolabi-Adesipe, has decried rising insecurity in the country. The actress, who was attacked by armed robbers on Tuesday, took to her Instagram on Wednesday to share her experience. She wrote: “No matter how much we scream and cry, it always falls on deaf ears of those who govern us even when death is involved,” she wrote. While narrating her ordeal, Kemi said the thieves cut her arm with a cutlass before taking her phones and other belongings and running off. “I am in a state of shock! Traumatised! I haven’t closed my eyes to sleep since yesterday. - Advertisement -   Duncan Mighty after accident: I’m hale, hearty     Southeast schools must sing Biafran anthem, IPOB threatens     Retired soldiers demand 24 months pension arrears   “I also experienced the highly poor insecurity state in Nigeria which has become a norm. “My driver and I were attacked by armed robbers at Arepo where I went to film while in traffic on our way back home. “They broke my windscreens, left my whole body with wounds and skin in pain because of the impact of the shattered glass which was forcefully broken while I was in the car. “My arm was cut with a cutlass; they took my phones, belongings and ran off! “Sadly my driver also took a hit to his head. “However, this is nothing compared to what I’ve been through in recent times. “No matter what may come my way, I will forever be grateful to God for preserving my life.”